  "body": "### Description\r\nAs someone interrogating the beaconchain, I want skipped slots not to return a block so that I know that they were skipped. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* When requesting a block from a skipped slot don't return a block, but some other result.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\nSlot 3 on Altona was skipped.\r\n\r\nFirst, query slot 2:\r\n```\r\n$ curl -sX GET \"http://localhost:5052/beacon/block?slot=2\"\r\n{\"root\":\"0xfd9f355f0ae6c4e09cced26aa1a69a53ec297ba2b497f766f189e17e4ea2defb\",...\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow, query slot 3:\r\n```\r\n$ curl -sX GET \"http://localhost:5052/beacon/block?slot=3\"\r\n{\"root\":\"0xfd9f355f0ae6c4e09cced26aa1a69a53ec297ba2b497f766f189e17e4ea2defb\",...\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that specifying slot 3 gets the same block as specifying slot 2.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nI honestly don't know whether the current behaviour is a bug or a feature. But I would like some way via the API to find out whether a slot was skipped (without having to compare root hashes).\r\n\r\nOn the whole, I think I'd prefer some other response than a block if the slot was skipped.\r\n\r\nNote that the API is going to change sometime, and we may prefer to deal with this at that time.\r\n",
